@startuml PKCE_Flow_Detailed
!theme blueprint
title PKCE (Proof Key for Code Exchange) Implementation Flow

actor User as U
participant "Frontend\n(blog.localtest.me:3000)" as FE
participant "Backend API\n(api.localtest.me:3001)" as BE
participant "Discord OAuth\n(discord.com)" as DC

== Phase 1: PKCE Parameter Generation ==
U -> FE: 1. Click "Login with Discord"
FE -> BE: 2. GET /auth/discord?lang=en

BE -> BE: 3. Generate PKCE code verifier
note right
**Secure Code Verifier Generation:**
// 32 bytes of cryptographically secure random data
const codeVerifierArray = new Uint8Array(32);
crypto.getRandomValues(codeVerifierArray);

// Convert to base64url (43-128 chars per RFC 7636)
const codeVerifier = btoa(String.fromCharCode(...codeVerifierArray))
  .replace(/\+/g, "-")    // Replace + with -
  .replace(/\//g, "_")    // Replace / with _
  .replace(/=/g, "");     // Remove padding =

**Properties:**
- Length: 43-128 characters
- Encoding: Base64url (URL-safe)
- Entropy: 256 bits minimum
- Character set: [A-Z][a-z][0-9]"-""."_""~"
end note

BE -> BE: 4. Generate PKCE code challenge
note right
**Code Challenge Generation (SHA256):**
// Use Web Crypto API for SHA256 hashing
const encoder = new TextEncoder();
const data = encoder.encode(codeVerifier);
const hashBuffer = await crypto.subtle.digest("SHA-256", data);
const hashArray = new Uint8Array(hashBuffer);

// Convert SHA256 hash to base64url
const codeChallenge = btoa(String.fromCharCode(...hashArray))
  .replace(/\+/g, "-")
  .replace(/\//g, "_")
  .replace(/=/g, "");

**Security:**
- Method: S256 (SHA256)
- One-way hash function
- Cannot derive verifier from challenge
- Prevents code interception attacks
end note

BE -> BE: 5. Store code verifier securely
note right
**Temporary Storage in HTTP-Only Cookie:**
set.cookie = {
  discord_code_verifier: {
    value: codeVerifier,
    httpOnly: true,           // XSS protection
    secure: false,            // HTTP in development  
    sameSite: "lax",         // CSRF protection
    maxAge: 10 * 60 * 1000,  // 10 minutes timeout
    path: "/",
    domain: ".localtest.me",
  }
};
end note

== Phase 2: OAuth Authorization with Code Challenge ==
BE -> DC: 6. Redirect to Discord OAuth (with PKCE)
note right
**Discord OAuth URL with PKCE:**
https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize
?response_type=code
&client_id=${CLIENT_ID}
&redirect_uri=api.localtest.me:3001/auth/discord/callback
&scope=identify%20email
&state=${state}|lang=${language}
&code_challenge_method=S256
&code_challenge=${codeChallenge}

**PKCE Parameters:**
- code_challenge_method: S256 (SHA256)
- code_challenge: Base64url-encoded SHA256 hash
- NO code_verifier sent
end note

DC -> DC: 7. Store code challenge

DC -> U: 8. Display authorization page
U -> DC: 9. Grant authorization

== Phase 3: Authorization Code Return ==
DC -> BE: 10. OAuth callback with authorization code
note right
**Callback Request:**
GET /auth/discord/callback
?code=AUTHORIZATION_CODE
&state=${state}|lang=en

**Security Properties:**
- Authorization code is short-lived (10 minutes)
- Code is bound to code_challenge in Discord
- Code is useless without matching code_verifier
- State parameter provides CSRF protection
end note

== Phase 4: PKCE Verification and Token Exchange ==
BE -> BE: 11. Extract and validate PKCE parameters
note right
**PKCE Validation Process:**
// Extract stored code verifier from cookie
const codeVerifier = cookie.discord_code_verifier?.value;

// Validate presence
if (!codeVerifier) {
  throw new Error("Missing code verifier cookie");
}

// Extract authorization code from callback
const code = query.code;
if (!code) {
  throw new Error("No authorization code received");
}

**Security Checks:**
1. Code verifier cookie exists
2. Authorization code present
3. State parameter validated (CSRF)
4. Request within time window (10 min)
end note

BE -> DC: 12. Exchange code for tokens (with PKCE proof)
note right
**Token Exchange Request with PKCE:**
POST https://discord.com/api/oauth2/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id=${CLIENT_ID}
client_secret=${CLIENT_SECRET}
code=${authorization_code}
grant_type=authorization_code
redirect_uri=${REDIRECT_URI}
code_verifier=${codeVerifier}

end note

DC -> DC: 13. Verify PKCE proof
note right
**Discord Server PKCE Verification:**
1. Retrieve stored code_challenge for this code
2. Hash the received code_verifier using SHA256
3. Base64url encode the hash result
4. Compare with stored code_challenge

if (base64url(sha256(code_verifier)) === stored_code_challenge) {
  // PKCE verification successful
  return access_tokens;
} else {
  // PKCE verification failed  
  return error;
}
end note

alt PKCE verification successful
    DC -> BE: 14a. Return OAuth tokens
    note right
    **Token Response:**
    {
      "access_token": "ya29.a0AfH6SMC...",
      "refresh_token": "1//04...", 
      "expires_in": 3600,
      "token_type": "Bearer",
      "scope": "identify email"
    }
    
    **Success Indicators:**
    - HTTP 200 OK status
    - Valid access_token received
    - Refresh_token for renewals
    - PKCE validation passed
    end note
    
    BE -> BE: 15a. Clear code verifier (security cleanup)
    note right
    **Security Cleanup:**
    // Clear the temporary PKCE cookie
    set.cookie = {
      discord_code_verifier: {
        value: "",
        maxAge: 0,                // Immediate expiration
        path: "/",
        domain: ".localtest.me",
      }
    };
    
    end note
    
else PKCE verification failed
    DC -> BE: 14b. Return error response
    note right
    **PKCE Failure Response:**
    {
      "error": "invalid_grant",
      "error_description": "PKCE verification failed"
    }
    end note
    
    BE -> FE: 15b. Redirect to error page
    note right
    **Error Handling:**
    - Log security incident
    - Clear all OAuth cookies
    - Redirect to login with error
    - User must restart flow
    end note
end

@enduml
